org.apache.ctakes.dictionary.lookup.ae

Interface LookupInitializer

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DirectLookupInitializerImpl, FirstTokenPermLookupInitializerImpl, FirstTokenPermLookupInitializerImpl

    public interface LookupInitializer
    Defines how to initialize the LookupAnnotator. NOTE: Constructor for implementation will be passed 2 arguments 1.) AnnotatorContext for accessing external resources 2.) Properties object for customization purposes.

      • getLookupWindowIterator

        java.util.Iterator<Annotation> getLookupWindowIterator(JCas jcas)
                                                       throws AnnotatorInitializationException
        Gets an iteration of windows. A window is used to scope which LookupToken objects are passed to the LookupAlgorithm.
        Parameters:
        jcas - Use the JCas to pull out pre-existing feature structures to build LookupAnnotation objects.
        Returns:
        Iterator over org.apache.uima.jcas.tcas.Annotation objects, each representing a window.
        Throws:
        AnnotatorInitializationException

      • getLookupAlgorithm

        LookupAlgorithm getLookupAlgorithm(DictionaryEngine dictEngine)
